<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As the clouds drew together in the sky guarding it with menace, it was clear something of great importance would occur this night. Lightning slicing the evening sky like blows from a great sword followed by the howling of a fallen foe. It was this night that a prophecy was started on it’s path and two boys were born. There was Ryvian, Gerial born in the grand city of Delnor. He was a small child with black hair and wondrous green eyes. The doctor was instantly shocked and horrified that a Gerial could have green eyes and not the fiery red like the rest of the race. His mother though held him close to her as he cried. In a city far to the south of Delnor another child was born with glorious white feather wings. His name was Mala Havoc, the great menace. He was born to lead the darklings back into power and open paths for the once beautiful messengers of the gods, to regain their might rule. This was the beginning of the foretold ware of wars. It is said to live in peace one must prepare for war, and the war is coming, but will the peace be restored?<br>
“Ryvian! The wisp is moving. We’ve got to catch it or it will get away,” shouted Amy. She was a fair skinned Gerial with long beautiful red hair and burning eyes to match. Ryvian had always admired her eyes and hair. He thought they made her look like the goddess of fire, Drephia. He poked his head out of the shrubs as his finely pointed ears twitched in the wind His tail swung back and forth above his head as he looked back to Amy.  “Amy, if you yell at me all the time you’ll scare it away.” He shushed her. The bright fairy floated on the breeze. The wisp with its small delicate wings and silvery hair drifted on an unfelt wind indifferent to its surroundings. The light emitted from its small form was bright enough to fill a room with its glow. The wisps were used as a source of light for the dark mountain passes. Ryvian pulled a jar from his pocket and crouched in the shrub ready to pounce. He saw the wisp get close to him and he waited for it to stop moving. He had told his father he could catch one and told his sister Amy that he could. The boys at his school had told him that he couldn’t, be he knew he could. There it stopped! Ryvian could feel every small muscle in the back of his neck grow tight. His green eyes burned with a passion as he leapt through the air; head first, for the wisp. He didn’t seem to see it but before he could do anything his instincts slammed his hands together closing the lid on the top.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Amy! I caught it! Look I did it!” Ryvian jumped up and down with glee as he looked into the glass. The young Gerials were one day away from reaching their next season. Ryvian and Amy were born on the same day one season apart. The seasons lasted for a span of five years, and were used as a way to tell maturity instead of age. Ryvian was turning his fourth and Amy her third. Ryvian was 5 years older than his sister and loved her more than anything in the world. He looked after her and protected her from some of the boys at their school who harassed her. Ryvian knew all of them and out of most of their school three boys gave her the hardest time. Joseph, Adam, and Nicholas were the meanest and roughest boys with her. Ryvian always stood up to them, but they were 3 years older then him and they would insult him for his eye color. They would call him Darkling and half breed even though he wasn’t. He was from the Avi bloodline and he knew his mother was not a Darkling and his father being the Warlord of the town, charged with the protection of Delnor. Delnor was to the north of the peninsula that the Gerials owned. It was cut off from the rest of the world by the natural mountains that peaked over the opening. Ryvian was just nineteen and was starting to look more like his father then a boy, with broad shoulders and black hair. He had a muscular tone to his shape and was strong for his age, but his eyes were still different from everyone he knew. All the Gerials were born with red eyes and he was the only one without them. He had started to feel so different that he was secluding himself from all activities, until his sister convinced him to come and play with her.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ryvian was going to be an Avi like his father. The bloodline of the Avi was very well trained. They were the elite fighting force of the land and sea. The reason for this is the trait that no one really understands other then the Avi, not even their counter part, the cleric. The Avi serve as a shield and sword for the cleric who will heal the Avi when needed. The Avi and the cleric are bound after their graduations. If one graduates before his cleric then they wait for each other. The two are soul mates and cannot be separated. If one of the two are placed with someone other then their soul mate, they will go insane and destroy each other. The Avi and cleric would eventually have two children, a son and daughter. The Gerials are allowed only two children if they have more then two it will be born with the power of the Avi and the magic of the cleric that would overwhelm the poor mind and push them past the boundaries of a sane mind.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Ryvian and Amy were dancing around now with the caught wisp. Amy gave Ryvian a kiss on the cheek and Ryvian smiled and winked at her. “You’re so brave Ryvian. I’m glad that finally came out of that hole that you call your room! I was beginning to think that you had forgotten me and left all alone in this boring town.” she smiled at him and giggled. Ryvian threw his arm over her shoulder as they walked back to his home. “I’ll always be there for you, I promise.” <br>
