&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Ryvian threw his hat down and slammed the jar on the counter. “All I want is to make him proud of me. I have one more day until I go off to training. He doesn’t even talk to me, just runs off whenever those damn horns of off I wish that we weren’t born in this family! I don’t want to be the son of an Avi and curse him for giving this gift to me! I caught a wisp for him.” Amy knew it was hard for Ryvian to go through this, but he was an Avi and this is what their lives were like. The two had lost their mother when they were young and never got much time with their father anymore. Amy had to leave to make it to her lesson with her teacher to be taught about healing. She felt bad for leaving Ryvian in his current mood. “I’m sorry Ryvian, but my Delphra is waiting. I’ll be back later.” Amy smiled as she shut the door behind her.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
She was going to get yelled at and maybe even a swatting if she was in enough trouble for being late. Amy had stayed back for just a few minutes to be with Ryvian. To her it had been worth the time. She didn’t know if it was the same for him, but it hurt her heart to be without him by her side. So she ran to get home to get the lesson over with as soon as possible. In the dead sprint she was in, Amy had tears in her eyes as the wind stung her with merciless gusts. She couldn’t see well and missed the three boys from her school that were ahead of her. They were smirking as they watched her running up towards them. The three were training wards, another part of the army; they were more or less the meat shields for a cleric as she battled her way through to help the wounded. Infantry was their job. They had been born 3 years before. They had lived for the honor of the military and to live up to their father’s life, but that didn’t stop them from pouncing on her as she ran by. Amy screamed as they grabbed her hair and punched her hard in her middle forcing the breath out of her lungs. She let out a small squeak as their hands roamed and groped at her body. She saw their eyes, filled with hate and malice, flash as they forced her to her feet and held her for each one to take a hit. She threw up as they let her fall to her knees, her long hair blowing in the violent breeze. She sent her thoughts to a far away place, the place she held on to her most dear ideas, thoughts of Ryvian and her love for him. She thought of him as tears fell from her perfect face, she felt no pity for herself, but for the three men that would feel the repercussions. She saw a box being dragged up and it looked that it could fit a person about her size very uncomfortably. They crammed her inside and kicked it a few times before covering it and running off. Lily’s world had gone from black of the box to white with pain.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Amy was brought to the forest that was used for hunting grounds when the town needed a food supply. The boys took her out of the box and shoved her out onto the ground. She bounced up ready this time for what was happening. She threw a punch just like Ryvian had taught her to, and caught Adam in his nose and another on his chin. Adam screamed out and fell backwards from shock. The other two grabbed her hair again and pulled her head back causing Amy to scream, she tried to kick, but they only grabbed her legs and pulled her to the ground. Adam still was rolling on the ground holding his face as Joseph and Nick started to tie her hands up and bind her ankles as well. When they had her tied down Adam got up and helped to carry her to a tree that was almost as wide as a house. Once they had dragged her up to the top the three opened a door that was made out of branches leading into the trunk of the tree. They shoved her in and laughed again as Joseph, the oldest of the three, walked in after her and closed the door of leaves. “Well if it isn’t my little butterfly. Well Amy where is your big brother to help you this time?” Jo smiled at her and knelt down to slowly start unbuttoning her shirt. “He’ll be here to save me, and you all will be sorry.” Amy said trying to sound strong, but failing. Jo laughed and lifted Amy’s chin. “I’m sorry to say, but if you bastard of a brother does show up then I am sure that my friends will be able to handle him. And as for the saving thing, why would you need saving? We all love you here, do you doubt us?” Jo smiled again as he took his knife from his belt and started to cut open her pants. Amy spat at him and tried to squirm. “Now, now darling, just settle down there I will be gentle I swear.” Jo leaned down next to her ear and whispered softly, “That is until I feel that you’ve been thoroughly broken in.” Amy tried to blink back her tears and put on a strong face as Jo wormed his strong hand in between her legs. With a smile he pulled her legs open as much as he could with her ankles still bound, and held them there with his knees. “I hate you! My brother is not a bastard and is not a half-breed! He’s a Gerial just like you, and he is an Avi!” Jo laughed as he unbuckled his belt. “I am sure he is. But we aren’t talking about him are we? No we are talking about you and me.” Laughter was heard from inside the trunk as well as the shouts of rape and pain. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Are you sure that this is such a good idea?” Nick asked Adam as he threw the tiny stones off the bridge of the tree fort that they had created as smaller children. Adam worked his sore jaw and pinched his nose, “I leave the thinking up to Jo and you should too. It pays off.” Nick swore as Amy’s shouts tore through the forest again and looked back at the trunk. “He’s really rough isn’t he? Well I think that his turn is over!” Nick swore again as he ripped the door open. “Jo! Get out now, you’ve had your fun, now it’s my turn!” Nick shouted with his sword pulled. Jo was inside the trunk between Amy’s legs sweat running down his back. “Damn you to the Dark Forest!” Jo said as he pulled his pants back up glaring at the sword as he shuffled out. Nick walked in with his sword still in his hands and was almost horrified when he turned to Amy. She was laying on the pull out bed with her legs twisted and tangled in the bloody sheets. There was not that much blood, but enough to make it visible. Nick shut the door, sword still in hands, and was enraged with himself when he saw the look of fear on Amy’s face. “I’m not going to hurt you, I’m not even going to touch you.” He said as he put his sword back away and walked to the bed. He laid a hand down on her leg as he took in her body wincing at some of the wounds that Jo must have delivered. “I’m sorry we did this to you. I just want you to know that it was never my idea, I always adored you, that has never been in question, but this is over the edge. I’m sorry that I can’t do anything but spare you any pain that I might pass on you.” Nick smiled as Amy visibly relaxed just a little. Nick had been a friend with Amy before he had fallen into the group of Jo and Adam. Nick was an Avi and the only one of the three friends. He had often played with the idea of Amy being his cleric. As he sat there covering Amy with a sheet he let her sleep with her head in his lap as he stroked her hair telling her how sorry he was. She had always trusted him and he was sure that she still did. It was now on him to protect her from the other two. If it cost him their friendship then so be it. He would not let them do this to her anymore. <br>
<br>
Ryvian had decided to go down to the beach north of his home after Amy left. The city he lived in was far to the north of the hutting peninsula that the Gerials owned. Mekings was the middle of the land where the King and his children lived. The old king of the Gerials had fought to protect their lands as his father and past generations had since the dark wars with the Darklings. That was before the gods took the messenger’s wings and forced the Darklings to become conquered. His wife had been killed by a raid on the fortress town by the Karz, a barbarian race of animal element worshipers. They lived far to the north and had a very strange way of life. After this he had turned around his sadness by making a truce with the northern foxes and restoring an edgy peace. Ryvian was thinking about this and his other history lessons when he got a terrible sense that something was wrong. He couldn’t quite decide what it was, only that it was important and it was tearing his heart out. He turned to the woods not looking where he was going. He walked his way absent-minded until he walked in to a branch and ended up on his back. Almost immediately he felt stupid and heard the laughing from a near tree. “Stupid Darkling can’t even walk!” the two boys in the tree fort ridiculed, pointing and laughing. They both had brown tunics on and looked to be playing a silly game where they had paint all over their faces and held a large fire near the clearing of the grove. Ryvian felt his ears grow hot as he glared at the boys, “Stop it guys. Jo, Adam, I’m not a Darkling and you know it. I was born right here in this town; you know my father.” he said. The boys laughed again and pointed. “Then where did your evil eyes come from!” they spat at him. Ryvian went through this everyday at school from the other children. His eyes weren’t the color of the others. He knew it and it would soon be at an end when he had a chance to prove himself. All the Avi started their training at their third season. He was going to show them all. He looked at one of the boy’s neck and saw the necklace that he had given Amy on her birthday. He instantly forgot his hurt pride as he searched the fort for the third boy. These two always had a third with them, always. He looked at the door of branches and listened carefully and heard what he thought was Amy crying. He clawed at the tree trying to climb up it. He made it half way when he was struck with a rock. He fell and looked back up to see two boys, grins gone, with their blades in hand. Ryvian swore as he ran off into the woods. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Amy had heard Ryvian outside the trunk of the tree. She thought about what had happened, the boys would be paid back for their games. She just hoped that she could tell him not to hurt Nick in time. She smiled as Nick held her hand and stroked her hair, and nuzzled against him again, he had not heard Ryvian outside she was fairly sure. She felt save enough with him, but was now worried about his safety. <br>
<br>
Nick nearly jumped at the shouts from his friends, as Adam wanted his turn. Amy was gripping on his hand tightly as the door was torn from the trunk. “Nick get out it’s my turn now. You’ve wasted your time I didn’t hear anything in here.” Adam smiled as Nick looked to the sword in his hand. “But this is wrong! Adam, I can’t let you do this, you can’t do this.” Nick stood freeing his hand from Amy. Just as his hand went for the hilt of his own sword, Nick was struck with an arrow in his shoulder and was knocked to the back wall. Adam rushed forward so Nick could have no room to pull his sword free. Amy stood up and tried to hold back Jo with a stick she had picked up from beside the bed. Jo grabbed it from her and smacked her across her face with it and lifted his bow nocking another arrow to the string. Amy cried again as she tackled him. Jo finally grabbed her again and threw her back to the bed tossing his bow he started back on her. Amy cried out and Nick with cuts on his arms and chest, and an arrow in his shoulder lunged forward with sword arm ready charged past Adam and pulled the blade free. Jo laughed again with a crazy gleam in his eyes as he yanked an arrow out of the quiver and took the sword blow in his side as he thrust the arrow point into Nick’s throat. “NO!” Amy screamed with tears falling from her face she kicked and punched and even tried biting Jo to get to Nick. He gurgled blood and fell forward. Amy broke free of Jo and held Nicks’ head. “Nick! Please don’t die, please, hang on for a moment let me fix it. I can fix it trust me I can.” Amy closed her eyes as she struggled with the door of her mind that held her power. She had to open the door and use the light on the other side to heal Nick. She felt the door start to open and let her mind travel over Nick’s wounds. She felt his life leaving and screamed as she kicked in the door in her mind letting the light rip into her mind flowing through her hands that were held above the gash in his neck. The wound started to fix itself and the muscles mended and intertwined again. The skin finally closed over the wound leaving no trace of the cut. She let her hands fall as she let out a sigh of relief as she closed the door. The light was dimmer and almost like a dark room when she was finished. The boys stepped out of the room as Nick struggled to sit up. “Nick don’t move, please just lie still. I’ll take care of you.” Amy smiled her special smile that she gave only to her brother and Nick and held his head. Nick chuckled and Amy leaned over to hear his whisper, “I thought that was my job.” She laughed as he tried to sit up. The other boys were shocked and scampered down the tree to make a plan of what to do. They had heard of a cleric’s power to heal, but never seen it. They had to get rid of her soon.<br>
