reen eyes as he threw the scabbard over his back fastening it there by the belt it came with, and then slinging his new shield over the scabbard making sure it was strapped tightly and that the hilt was clear of any obstacles. He ran back to the fort with a mission, to kill all of the boys. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Amy had held her ground when Adam tried to get in and Nick was in no condition to fight to protect her. Jo, and Adam had made their plans and started them into play. First, Adam hid behind a pile of tree branches next to the door. Jo had worked on a rope system and had it set up right in the path of the doorway. They called and begged and then decided to just let her think they had left. In a few minutes it had worked, Amy had started out the door when Jo pulled the rope tight catching her legs and Adam pounced on her pulling her by the rope out onto the clearing of the tree fort. She had pulled together most of her clothes and was again stripped of them as she screamed and tried to kick. Jo moved fast and grabbed her hands and tied them to a post that they had readied. Nick was asleep trying to regain his energy and was so deeply sleeping that he heard nothing as he dozed. Amy screamed again as Adam forced her knees open and smiled at Jo. The two snickered and Amy tried to pull her legs together. They laughed at her efforts and Adam loosed his pants down wormed his fingers into the squirming Amy. “Please stop!” she cried as he smiled again licking his fingers. “We’ll stop after one last ride, we swear.” Adam snarled as he stopped her wiggling by grabbing her hips and plunging in between her legs. She let out a scream that rendered their ears as the blood began to flow anew down her legs. <br>
<br>
Hours later after the two had raped her many times they tied her to a pole that was hung between two tripods down next to their fire. She was covered in sweat and blood out of tears she looked at the two move about as she felt her body ache. Where were her protectors, she thought as the boys moved her closer to the fire setting up two more posts to hold the pole she was tied to. She looked at the boys working her sore jaw where Adam had hit her a few times, and tried to talk to them. Her voice didn’t work as she cried and felt something in her break. The boys stopped their working and turned to her looking at her body and smiling again. The oldest one, Jo opened his mouth to say something, but instead his eyes rolled to the back of his head as only blood and no words came out of his mouth. She looked at the body fall to the ground and the bloody blade that stayed where the man once stood. She followed the tip of the blade finding the dragons engraved to be very intricate and beautiful, to the hilt with fingers wrapped tight. She saw a strong Gerial with hair as black as the night robbed it’s mistress moon. His face was handsome and jaw set. She looked at last into his eyes, burning with a fire that could be matched by no flame. Eyes that could melt any warrior’s temperance, and make her heart soar all at once, green. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Adam shouted in fright as he saw his friend fall to the ground, he quickly picked up his sword and looked from Ryvian to Amy. He decided he would have to kill her first to have any chance to make it out of this forest alive. He ran and kicked over the structure holding her near the fire knocking her into the flames. With a bout of flame the fire that had been fed and fueled all day consumed Amy. Ryvian was almost too shocked to react to the action as the blade swung toward his head. Ryvian shouted as swords met and Ryvian blocked and quickly stuck again. Having his blow parried Ryvian ducked under a swing and spun. The boy’s sword struck the shield on Ryvian’s back and as was knocked clear from his hands by the recoil. With an upward motion Ryvian thrust his blade into his enemy’s chest. The blade went effortlessly through his ribs as Ryvian picked the boy off his feet. He gritted between his teeth to the boy, “This is for my sister you gods forsaken son of a whore!” he snarled and flung him towards the tree. The boy shouted as he flew and let a grunt from his throat as a branch impaled him. “You wanted to play war with me! Boys! I was born for it!” Ryvian shouted<br>
<br>
In his rage Ryvian had killed Adam and was rushing over to the flames to where Amy had rolled. She was badly burned and nearly gone by the time Ryvian got there. It had happened so fast he hadn’t even gotten time to save her from it. She opened her eyes and looked into her brother’s face. Ryvian leaned over as she kissed him on the cheek. “Brother, I want to go home. Please take me home. Ryvian, don’t hurt Nick, he’s up in the fort and tried to protect me as much as he could. Ryvian I bonded to him, they had cut him badly and I had to do it. I had to in order to save him. I had to heal him for his help. Tell father that I was going to training. Ryvian please promise me that you will keep your head up, whatever happens don’t let people get you to doubt yourself.” Ryvian was choking on his tears as he held his sister’s bloody hair. “Amy please, please don’t leave me here.” Ryvian cried to no avail she was already gone. Death had not been anything like he had thought, he thought he could swoop in and save her but it had happened too fast and he had waited too long. Ryvian cried over his sister and lifted her after a time to take her home as he had promised. <br>
