 <br>
&quot;Dear Ryvian, <br>
I know you can never forgive me for taking the sister that you loved and adored, but trust me when I say that I did not mean to do this, I loved her closely and she healed me when I was near death. We were perfect for each other in the situation and I would have made it my life's intent to make her happy for all of her days. I know the pain you go through for Amy as I go through a similar feeling, only I must take mine further than yours. Tomorrow’s sunrise will be my last as I look at the sun that Amy will never see again and take with me the images back to the gates of the Dark Forest, where she wait for me in the afterlife.<br>
Avi Nicholas.” <br>
<br>
Nick left the note on his desk as he went out to look at the sky. He had left the note addressed to Ryvian and hoped that he would get it. He wished that he could go back in time and change the way things were, but as he began to wonder why life played this trick on him Nick thought he saw flames coming from the dock and a winged creature fly off into the sun. Nick spat at the ground as he ran back into the house grabbing his father’s spear on the way out the door. He now had one last mission to finish before he left. He felt that if he killed that monstrosity with wings that he would be allowed to enter the Dark Forest with his love Amy. He only prayed that she wait for him there.<br>
