&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ryvian had caught some of the news but had stopped listening when he heard his father had died. “How?” The three men looked at him, “A darkling was leading the charge on out naval fleet and seemed to have taken us by such surprise that he managed to take out several ships on his own. This Darkling started such uproar that it took us three large formations to finally get him to run. He had wings Ryvian. Your father and him battled on the deck and Destri lost. It was a close battle, your father pulled him down on the deck and lured him to fight him on the ground, but after he had inflicted many wounds on him the Darkling took off and came back throwing his sword down at your father who caught it in his chest.” The major said as he unbuckled a sword from his belt and set it on the table. “This was his. I’m sure he wanted you to have it. Me and him go way back you know, we fought together in the fort of Zefi.” The major said eyes cast down. Ryvian looked at the blade and saw the three lions and two tigers engraved on the scabbard of his family crest. He knew that the blade itself was of such a fine metal that it was a sword that almost never dulled. He lifted it as the men stood. “We have many more messages to give, I’m sorry lad.” The three men started to walk to the door, “Wait, one of you are the head chief of the Avi, after my father, right?” Rvyain asked looking from his chair. The man that turned was a strong built Gerial with long hair pulled back into a knot. “I’m of my forth season and am joining today. I have nothing here to keep me back so I will go with you.” Ryvian stood as the men waited for him to gather his things. He walked back out of his room with his chain mail armor, his father’s sword at his waist, and the hilt of the other blade jutting over his shoulder, the shield strapped tight on top of the scabbard. Ryvian looked at his house once again spotting the spear that was passed down from generation to generation he grabbed it from the wall as he shut and locked the door. All his memories were nothing and he was about to start his life.  He would now do what his father always wanted him to do, take his place with honor. His mission in life was to take the wings of the monstrosity that killed his father and have his vengeance.<br>
