&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Years went by and Ryvian had moved to the top of his class. The students didn’t make fun of his eyes and he grew to understand that the Avi were leaders for a reason. They didn’t have to relish in the mocking of others to get ahead. Instead they fought hard and long all their lives. In all the missions and activities Ryvian had gathered more spirits then anyone else and had ventured higher into the mountain passes then anyone in his class.  He had broken records set many years ago in his efficiency. He had gathered yet another blade when he killed a Griffin with his bare hands. They took the blood from it and used it to dye his sword a reddish hue with the tigers and lions on the blade adding it to his back. He had grown to a position of respect and honor. As he grew, so did his experience and his armor. They made the armor out of a special material found in the passes that made it very strong and dyed it with the blood of the cobalz to give it a green hue and protection against the most powerful spells. The color green was to help determine an Avi from his wards. The days of work were beginning to pay off as he strolled the city of Mekings where he would gather the last part of his armor and receive his honors and graduate. He had waited for one hundred years to finally get to where he was. During the many seasons of his training he had gotten many letters from Lily, only reading one or two and burning the rest. Distractions would have hindered his learning. The two things he did on his leave were to see Lily graduate, although she didn’t see him there, and to attend her mother and brother’s funeral. Both times he hadn’t talked to Lily, or even let her know he was there.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ryvian had grown strong not only in arm, but in mind. He knew of every race in the documented world, and even some more. He learned from them everything, including the way of war. He had made his style from the many forms all combined.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He had been in the grand city of Mekings for five days now and didn’t even notice the crowds of people that seemed so natural in such a large area. In all his life, Ryvian had seen wonderful places and large cities and forests, but   the people made this town look all that much bigger. The city was constructed during the times of the Darkling rule. It held three sections in the main walls, the slums, making the outer section surrounding the rest closest to the walls, then the market and upper class residential circled with a wall blocking out the slums and the fort. The fort was were the King and his royal family resided. The walls were higher then the rest of the town, and in the center stood the tower of the Avi guard piercing the heart of the clouds with its height. Cutting the first two sections in the middle, the merchant road was made up of all of the working class and was the life of the city. The road ran all the way up to the main gates of the fort. Ryvian was amazed at the beauty of the city and the sheer genius of the town’s structure. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp For the first few days he stuck to the middle section of the city wandering around looking at all of the people and the merchants. After that he decided to take a trip into the slums, but as soon as he got there he found himself out of place and quickly left. Then on the last day he decided to take a look at the fort, after all this is where his bloodline all started. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He woke up that morning and looked out his window to see the walls towering over his inn and made his mind up that he would go and see it himself. As he wandered to the gate of the fort he saw the arrow slits in the twin towers sitting on either side of the thick wooden gate. It was surrounded by a moat that was not large, but would certainly put doubt into a mind trying to take the fort. The guards standing on the bridge at the fort stared at some unseen foe with faces set. Ryvian strode to the men and looked at them. He had been wise to wear the armor of the Avi today and smiled, as the guards moved aside quickly not looking him in the face. Ryvian chuckled to himself as he moved past them into the open gates of the fort. Even though he was not a complete Avi yet he was allowed past them into the fort due to his armor, only and Avi could gather this armor and only an Avi would even dare to wear it.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ryvian had been in the fort for a few hours looking at all the grand towers and banners. He had even seen part of the armory. The day’s sun was reaching its full glory when Ryvian knew he had to be getting back to his inn and ready for the graduation. With the sound of all the people and the many turns in the path, Ryvian was not paying attention to where his surroundings as he turned the corner and ran into a girl. “I’m sorry I didn’t see you there.” He offered his hand to help her back to her feet. After she stood up Ryvian noticed that she was glancing over her shoulder nervously. Ryvian eyed her age, she could be no more then 2 seasons younger then he, and she had extraordinary eyes. They burned with a fire that seemed to consume everything, looking deeper into them, Ryvian found not only fiery defiance, but also intelligence. He was caught off guard by her eyes and it took him a moment to gather his thoughts. He was wondering why a girl like this was in street garb, dressed like a peasant, although there was something about the way she held herself, straight backed, head high, and chin raised. She didn’t seem the type to be left out in the road. Again his smile faded at his thoughts, but seeing the nervousness in her eyes changed his stare into a grin. “I’m Ryvian the Surefooted. I’ am an Avi and am glad to be at your service, lass.” He bowed with a smile. She looked over her shoulder again. “I’m Rylena. I seem to be lost.” She gave a little bout. Ryvian grinned, this girl was more then she seemed to be. She would not have been able to just wander this area of the town. Ryvian was about to say something witty when he was knocked to the ground. “In the name of all that is good and holy!” Ryvian shouted as he drew to a standing position with his hand wrapped tightly around the hilt of the sword that jutted over his right shoulder. His eyes finally found his assailant. “Sister! What are you doing talking to him? Why are you dressed like that? Why are you not with your guards? Damn it!” the boy shouted. The boy’s eyes moved to Ryvian once again. Rylena was standing with a frown on her face and the look of a defeated escapee. Ryvian finally took in the boy’s appearance fully and saw a young Gerial, finely dressed. He wore a small blade at his side and a tilted hat on his head. The boy saw the hand on the hilt and instantly drew his sword and stepped between Ryvian and Rylena. “You dare threaten my sister with your sword! I’ll have you head for that!” The young boy charged at Ryvian. Now really confused Ryvian drew his sword as the boy struck. The blade struck his cloak and slid harmlessly off his green armor underneath. Ryvian took the opportunity to fight back. He struck with sure moves and ease of experience. The boy dodged most of the swings and blocked the others; he was very energetic. Finally putting an end to the young boy’s foolishness, Ryvian quickly hit the hilt of the boy’s sword knocking it into the air where Ryvian snatched it in his other hand. The boy moved to pull a dagger but his sister stepped in between the two. “Will you two stop this!” she shouted at them. “I’m not in danger Talidon, I was in perfectly good hands.” The boy moved his hand away from his dagger and outstretched it to Ryvian gesturing to his sword. “No, first I want some answers. What was that all about? I’m Ryvian Surefoot, head of the Avi class, and Warlord to the town of Delnor. Who the hell are you!” Ryvian was very unnerved as he slowly lowered his own sword. “I am Talidon Darkwind, this is my sister Rylena Darkwind. I am Prince of the Sword and the royal heir to the throne of the Gerials!” he snapped back. Ryvian dropped the boy’s sword in shock and saluted. “I’m sorry sir, but you attacked me.” The young boy glared at him and then his sword. Ryvian picked it up and placed it in the hands of his prince. “Well sister, it is time we get back to father.” He said as he slammed his sword into his scabbard and hooked his arm with Rylena’s. She was hauled away but still looked back with a smile to Ryvian. After they were out of sight Ryvian could only let a sigh of relief and lift his sword with a slow hand.<br>
