eir minds. The Avi finds the ore by the lake of the lost stars in bar form. The miners created their forges by the water to create the bars of highly durable and very light metal. Not only is there danger from the miners but there are also creatures called Milthis, lurkers of the shadows. It is believed that the miners had been testing on some creatures to find a suitable opponent for the Darklings. They called this the project of forgotten souls. The Avi gain most of their knowledge from these creatures if found. They have been on Nevil since the beginning of time and lived through the wars of the Light as well as the early wars with the Naltrans. After the ore is collected it is brought back to the surface to be turned into the armor of an Avi with the help of the instructors the student creates it with the seals and the blood of the cobalz to make it impenetrable to magic. This process is done the student is allowed to wear his armor to protect him as the pieces only get harder and harder to collect for. There are three different styles of the armor that is created to show rank and ability. The scaled being the topmost ranking as the design is much more intricate then the others; the plated armor that is worn by most of the Avi and is a symbol of hard work and dedication, and finally the chained armor is the sign of a more or less skilled Avi. They are the ones that are assigned as lower officers to run the ships of the mighty ocean fleet of the Gerials. Ryvian was receiving the scaled armor for his research in the caves of the lost, and his many adventures that brought him fame and respect form many of the other Avi. He bowed his head as he took his helm that his Commander had created for him, the scaled dragon’s head that resembled the dragons on his sword. He had three swords, his father’s sword strapped to his back, the dragon’s blade strapped crisscross to his father’s and then the blade that he was gifted from the Griffon at his hip. He wore them with pride as each had given him a part of the arsenal that would be needed in his future battles. The Griffon blade not only gave him another weapon, but also granted him the power of sight. He could see far away as if he had eyes in the blue sky as well as the ground. Ryvian stood with his new helm and smiled to the crowd and took his place standing next to the Commander as he handed out the rest of the armor, none of them scaled, as the crowd cheered them on.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp After the ceremony Ryvian started his walk away from the crowds. He was very proud of himself to have gotten the high honor of a scaled helm to go along with his armor. He was now the noted Warlord of the city of Delnor with the sign of his graduation. His job was to protect the people of Delnor from any force that might pose harm. As his road took him to a intersection a wave of anxiety washed over him and it was not his. “I see the dashing man I once knew and loved walking down the same street as I. You’re just as handsome if not more then when I last saw you.” As the familiar voice reached his ears he stopped but did not turn. “Thank you very much, I worked very hard for this day.” His head dropped a little, “I heard about your mother and Henri. I’m sorry.” He turned around to face Lily and caught his breath in his throat. He was surprised, and at first Lily thought he was disappointed and gave him a small pout. She was wearing a purple dress of the finest material that made her appear to be floating. She had grown taller and her hair was long and braided. Ryvian smiled again as he moved closer to her. Already feeling the draw to her Ryvian stopped a few paces from her. “Well, you certainly are looking as beautiful as ever. My imagination of what the pretty little girl I once knew would look like was not near as beautiful as you are now.” Her face was that of pure joy and she let out a small giggle that was like drops of dew in a crystal pond. “I was sorry to hear about your father, I didn’t see you after that day and couldn’t tell you how sorry I was. I also lost my father to that horrible day. I sent you mail everyday, but I guess you didn’t get it. I told you about my graduation and how I cried because I didn’t see you there. I also wrote you that I was coming to see yours and where I would be staying.” She smiled again faintly. Ryvian took her into his arms and held her as she rested her head on his shoulder. “It has been too long my sweet flower.” Ryvian said as he listened to her soft tears of joy. Then she backed away, wiping the tears from her eyes, “It has indeed.”  The two hooked arms as they walked down the road to the ball being held at the King’s court.<br>
