<br>
Ryvian walked through the main hall after a servant took his cloak. The pair walked into the grand ballroom, Ryvian leading with his hand guiding the small of Lily’s back. The surrounding room was filled with tables and Avi. There was a grand space open for dancing and there was even an orchestra playing. Ryvian was on edge about the place, he couldn’t tell why, but the amount of people made the hairs on his neck stand on end. Taking in the surroundings the room was beautiful. There were grand tapestries hanging on the walls of the great wars, of heroes, and of enemies. He was so taken by the room that he nearly missed the music coming to an end. He looked back to Lily with a childish grin, “Almost as enchanting as you, but not quite.” Lily smiled as Ryvian swept her into an embrace as the music started up again.<br>
<br>
The two danced for a few songs and when Lily grew tired the two moved to a table. As the guards moved like silent stalkers in a great jungle, a man in a suit walked to the table to pour wine for the two of them. He nearly missed the cup when he saw Ryvian’s eyes. “Sir, was your mother of a different race than us? Did your father dilute the blood of the Avi with your birth?” The waiter said awfully rude. “No my mother was of our race and my father was the Warlord of Delnor, and he knew not to do such a foolish thing. And if you have a problem with me then please don’t skip around it and tell me now.” Ryvian said growing more agitated. The man fumbled an apology and staggered off into the sea of people. Ryvian shook the encounter off and lifted his glass. “Well, may we life happy lives, long and together.” Lily smiled and Ryvian saw the reason he loved her. The red eyes flashed and all her beauty and intelligence, and splendor shone through. As the two started in on the steak that had been set for them Ryvian felt the hair on the back of his neck really stand on end. His hand went to the hilt of his blade, his father’s sword, the one he wore for this occasion at his hip, to see if it was clear in the scabbard. The music started up again with a fast movement when a familiar voice sounded at his back. “Well, well. If it isn’t the half breed.” Ryvian moved his chair back and looked at the speaker. “Thomas. I see you still have the same misconception that plagued you in school. You just can’t understand that I’m better than you.” Thomas pulled his sword free and kicked over a nearby table, “That’s it Ryvian! I’ve had enough of you and your stubborn attitude. I had to live with you from day one and now I’m going to end it.” Ryvian smirked as he stood up motioning for Lily to stay seated. “Well if you want, I’ll gladly take this outside with you and see who really is the best.” Ryvian patted his sword and gave Thomas a lazy smile. “I suggest you bring your cleric. I hope she’s had enough training to put you back together when I’m done with you.” Thomas turned red, “No, Ryvian this time I decide the place. Here now.” Ryvian smiled and turned back to Lily who had a worried look. “Darling this won’t take long, I promise.” Turning back to Thomas, “Let’s take this into the open area.”<br>
<br>
Ryvian stood back turned to Thomas as a crowd circled around them on the dance floor. He was watching Lily give him a worried and somewhat concerned look. Ryvian turned his attention back to Thomas. “Well let’s get this show on the road. Ladies and gentlemen, I am Ryvian the Surefooted, Warlord of Delnor, and this is a friend of mine, his name is Thomas. Sadly Thomas here has no cognomen and has no current role. He has challenged me to a duel to the death, and as a Gerial of good will, I will fight this without the use of my cleric.” Ryvian again looked at Lily who looked more than worried at the moment. “And please one more thing, this is a duel, please do not interfere. Thank you all, I hope this will bring you some entertainment.” Ryvian bowed to the people as he pulled his sword and knelt. “Father be with me tonight.” He said quietly to himself. Thomas drew his own sword and the crowd was tingling with excitement. This was not a normal event; the Avi rivalries were usually not seen and very covered up. The ring of the blade told Ryvian it was time and he stood taking his stance. Both Gerials glared at each other in perfect stance from across the space. Ryvian smiled again as Thomas broke his stance to charge. Blades met and Ryvian was forced back. The two struck and parried blows with styles that made it look more like a dance of deadly proportions. Lily hid her face as Ryvian was struck in his sword arm. Thomas was pressing all his strength into the blows and exhausting his energy quickly. Ryvian was more reserved in his blows and had struck in places that were slowly bleeding Thomas of his energy. Thomas’ cleric was busy healing away as Ryvian swung with the sure strokes that took their toll on Thomas.<br>
Across the room watching the two fight, were two children, one gazing with eyes that could not be broken from Ryvian, and the other imitating the moves he saw. The two Gerial royalties were standing in front of their father. The guards standing around the King and his children were taking bets on the winner. While the crowd cheered and groaned at the strikes, Lily was slowly opening the door to her magic while the moon was still most powerful. <br>
<br>
Ryvian had still not given his mind over yet as Thomas switched back and forth trying desperately to stay in the fight. Finally scoring a shot that was near fatal Thomas grinned. “Ryvian it seems that I will go home with your woman tonight!” he snarled through gritted teeth. Ryvian growled and swung his father’s sword slicing Thomas’ blade in two. The force of it took Thomas off his feet and on his back. Instantly trying to sit up he met a blade at his throat. “I told you that I would kill you for this.” Ryvian gasped trying to regain his breath. Lily was at his side in a heartbeat, “Ryvian, you’ve beaten him. Leave him be now, you have beaten him.” Ryvian was on his last nerve when he sheathed his sword. He turned to Lily and held her in his arms for a moment. He was exhausted and sore from the fight. Lily helped him back to their table and he smiled at her once again finally able to take a full breath. She smiled back at him, eyes sparkling. Ryvian was at peace again and was gazing into Lily’s eyes when he noticed something. They had changed from her dazzling red to a deep hazel. He was shocked and he noticed that the smile was also gone from her beautiful face. He was about to ask what was wrong but he knew. He turned again and saw the fire blaze as Thomas dropped the dagger and fell to the ground in a roar of flames. Ryvian looked again and saw Lily’s eyes change back over to the red that he always remembered. He was about to say something, but decided not to. Instead he smiled at her again and kissed her hand. <br>
<br>
The crowd had fallen back form the Gerial on fire with gasps and then moved back together as the King himself moved towards Ryvian’s table. “Excuse me. I was wondering if I could have a word with you.” Ryvian was shaken out of his thoughts as he turned to find Justin the Large, King of the Gerials. He was standing behind his seat with a smile on his face. Ryvian fell out of his chair landing on his knees in a bow, “Sir.” The King chuckled and put a large hand on his shoulder. “You may stand. What is your name?” Ryvian shuffled to his feet standing straight. “I am Ryvian the Surefooted, top of my Avi class and Warlord of Delnor, by birthright. Sir.” The King smiled. The crowd again parted and Ryvian saw two Gerials come running to the King’s side. Ryvian smiled as Rylena and Talidon hugged their father and looked towards him. “So tell me Ryvian, what did this man do to provoke you into the fight?” Ryvian smiled and looked to the still smoking body of Thomas, “Well, sir, I have known that Avi from the moment we started school. He was determined to be the top and refused to recognize my superiority, not that it bothered me, but when he pushed it to mocking and insulting, I could do nothing else but defend the name of the Avi and kill the weak link that threatened the chain of centuries of strong Avi.” Ryvian said confidently. He was sure that he was not in any kind of wrong for killing Thomas. “Well I totally agree. The Avi have always been the elite of this land and will always be that. To be elite we must rectify the weak. Well spoken indeed. Ryvian I want you to meet my children. This is Rylena, and this is Talidon.” The two children stepped forward and Rylena smiled at Ryvian. “These are my most precious treasures, and I want you to train them. You and your cleric that is, I’m sorry to have been so rude, but I didn’t catch your name.” The king said as he kissed Lily’s hand. “Rylena smiled again at Ryvian. “Sir, I don’t think I understand. You want me to train your son? Why not send him to the school of the Avi, and same with your daughter? They would get better care and much more efficient training. Also sir, if Lily, and myself are called off to a war then what of your children? Sir.” The King smiled. “Listen, since you are going to be my children’s teacher, then you should call me at least by my name. And Justin works just fine.” With that the King turned and started to leave. “I have trusted in you now, Ryvian the Surefooted, as I did with your father, I expect to keep that trust.” The King then walked off into the crowd. <br>
