<br>
 Just as he had found her and started to kiss her, there was a knock at the door followed by the sound of the door being opened. Ryvian was out of the bed in a rush and already had sword in his hands before he knew who it was. He was within a span of a feather of delivering the killing blow to the neck before he looked into the face of the young runner. With a growl he dropped his sword back into the mess on the floor and walked back to the bed where Lily was just sticking her head above her cave in the covers. The runner was white with fright and was shaking when Lily looked at Ryvian with a silly grin. “You big jerk you scared the wits out of the messenger. Look at him he can’t even get a word out now.” Lily giggled and Ryvian threw another pillow at her, Lily ducking back into the bed. “Sorry about that. I wasn’t sure who you were and you just barged into my room.” Ryvian smiled trying to ease the frightened runner. “Well, sir, I was just out of breath. You caught me off guard, sorry.” Ryvian grinned, “You’re joking right? You caught me off guard, I should have known it was a messenger, but I was kind of sidetracked.” Ryvian smiled nodding back at the bed. The runner grinned, “Well sir, the Commander is calling everyone to the main hall. You have until the bells ring for midday.” The runner smiled back at Ryvian looking to the bed, “You’re a lucky Gerial, she’s beautiful.” Ryvian smiled again and thanked the runner as he showed him out. <br>
As Ryvian opened the doors to the barracks that served as the main hall of the Army, he saw hundreds upon hundreds of wards walking around and in the center of them all one green clad Avi. He was looking at the weapons on the walls when he stumbled into a man who was shouting orders to a group of nearby Avi. “You boys be careful, I need you to take the wards and move them down the map to here. Then stay put until you are met by the side fleet before proceeding to Zefi.” The Avi nodded and took their maps off the table and turned back to their wards to walk out the door. Ryvian caught the Commander by the arm before the crowd ate him into the folds of people. “Sir, Ryvian the Surefooted reporting.” The Gerial turned and Ryvian was nearly shocked. It was Mettrich, the guard from the other night. “Good morning Ryvian.” Mettrich smiled at the surprised Avi. Grinning Mettrich lead the way to the table with a large map of the world on it. “We are in some trouble young man. The Darkling fleets are proving more and more dangerous with the use of the winged fleet as well as the navel.” Ryvian grabbed the Commander’s shoulders and pulled him around to face him, “You said winged? I only knew of one winged Darkling!” Ryvian nearly shouted. The Commander chuckled, “You are far behind in current events. The Darklings have produced more then two fleets of winged generations, and our sources tell us that they are in league with the Humans of the south. They have taken out our post Zefi and taken to building ships for the Darklings to help them move around. Our scouts tell us that they have already brought great damage to the northern lands of the Tundra Foxes. They have fought them off so far, but also have taken large losses. We need you to take a Galton of twelve wards and your cleric to the human city. There you are to remove the central government and replace it with yourself until our ambassador gets there to take control. You might find some resistance along the way, so I suggest you bring the spear that your father used to own. It can be used against a winged Darkling. I’m sure with your background, as a child in the fishing town Delnor, you will know your way around throwing a spear.” The Commander handed Ryvian the papers of pass through Valin’s pass, and maps of the areas. Ryvian was still in a state of shock as he looked at the map on the table. “You want me to travel all the way across the world away from my home to go on a stupid mission that could be carried out by a mere ambassador?” Ryvian was past shock as his temper rose. “Ryvian. I am not sending you for that one mission; I am testing the strength of the Human-Darkling alliance. I want to see the reaction when our race takes the city on not just this war, but with the entire of the world. If we find that the people hate the rule and will make war on us we take out the human royalty and leave it for the council to decide. That is why I’m sending you. You are of vital importance to the safety of our way of life. If you do not succeed in the objective, then we will have no information and the Humans will still be at the back of the Darklings.” The Commander looked at Ryvian, and then behind him to the awaiting wards. “This is your Galton, Ryvian lead them well.” With that the Commander was swept off into the crowd followed by Avi and wards that had lined up next to him awaiting orders.<br>
<br>
The wards lined up in order from rank, the badges of battle were adorned above their right arm. Ryvian looked from the first one to the last one with a keen eye. He noted their reactions as they looked into his green eyes. “We move out at dusk. Gather your things and say goodbye to anyone that knows you because we are heading into a dangerous area. I will meet you at the front outside the gates after the bell has struck three more times today, midday has just pasted. I will meet all of you and I expect you to be in your armor and with lances and swords.” Ryvian looked again at the wards and sighed. This was what he was given to take a whole city! This was ridiculous to take a small Galton that doesn’t even fit up to a royal guard for the King’s son and take over a city. This was madness. <br>
