<br>
As Ryvian watched as Talidon danced around with sword in hand fighting an invisible enemy. Ryvian threw advise to the young Avi as his sister giggled with glee as she watched her brother practice. Lily had her hands full with the questions from her own charge. Rylena was constantly asking questions that were about magic as well as Ryvian. The young girl was almost obsessed with her curiosity for the Avi. Lily smiled when Ryvian sighed out frustration showing her that she was not alone in this. She loved the two like her own children, but this was ridiculous, they were trained for war and duty, not teaching. <br>
<br>
Ryvian told his two new charges that they would need to pack because they were moving on a mission to take the human city. The two were so excited that they ran off into the streets knocking over a stand. Talidon asked if he could bring his cleric, as he already had one. It would just make things easier for the both of them if they could be together. Ryvian agreed. He would have to loan him some proper armor, and Lily would have to teach the cleric some things if she was not already through her school. This was getting complicated. Ryvian sighed again only with relief when he was finally alone with Lily in the room to get their own things together. “Those two will be the death of me. By the time we get to Ibium I will be begging the humans to kill me then.” Lily chuckled. “I think Rylena has fallen in love with you. Now I’ll have to find myself another Avi.” She said in a playful pout. “Ha, that child could not take your place, in my heart, not even a glimpse.” Ryvian snickered. “She is too young to understand the ways of life.” Lily smiled again as she looked up from her packing. “You have to admit that she does resemble her just a little.” Ryvian stopped with his lance in one hand and bags in the other. “Yes she does.” Ryvian said shortly and walked out the door.<br>
<br>
Lily looked back at her bags and remembered back to their childhood, to that night that Amy was killed. Ryvian was hurt by the memory, and with Rylena, a striking resemblance to her, this could grow complicated. Lily shed a tear for the memory and walked out after Ryvian. This would indeed be a hard trip on them all.<br>
