<br>
The bells rang out over the peaceful city of Mekings as Ryvian and his Galton marched out of the city.  The troop was adorned with armor and lances rested in the loop in the saddle of their horses. Ryvian had taught Talidon to ride with his lance locked securely in place. Lily was riding next to Rylena talking about how the bond could be felt when she had chosen her Avi, and how the healing for the first time would be done. Talidon’s cleric was also listening intently. Ryvian had listened to the Galton’s complains about taking untrained recruits, but when told the King had insisted they each grumbled less often and quieter. <br>
<br>
“Ryvian, how does an Avi know that the soul he has control of is trustable?” Talidon asked as the Galton started to set up camp. The troop had made it half way out into the plains that lead from the main city of Mekings, to the mountain pass that would lead out into the world. Ryvian smiled as he watched the sun slowly set behind the mountains. “Well, in death the souls of those that we take into our own, become peaceful and all resentment and loathing or hatred that was once the driving force is replaced with a peace that only death can bring to one. In a way the Avi lets a person become longer lived through our own life. That way the souls we hand over our trust to are glad to help the living. At times though we encounter a soul that is deeply dangerous to our safe being; a person so filled with hate that they can not be soothed in death and must there for be sent on to the afterlife without a chance, you will learn how to let a soul pass through you instead of enveloping it and making it part of yourself.” Ryvian finished. As he stood up he saw Rylena gazing at him from inside her tent. When he winked at her she blushed and retreated back into the tent. Ryvian was confused, but he soon forgot his thoughts when he caught Lily’s eyes following him as well. He smiled her direction and she smiled lovingly back to him. He started to cross the expanse when he ran into Maternic. “Sir I was just looking for you. I wanted to talk to you about some of the others; they have problems that need to be brought to attention, mainly yours.” Ryvian nodded and started to walk to his command tent. Once inside Ryvian had the ward’s full attention. It seemed to Ryvian that this Gerial was the leader of the Galton before they were assigned to him. “Well,” Ryvian asked as he poured a glass of yaltin, a sweet wine. “Well sir there are some of the Gerials that are more than loyal and willing to fight, but there has been some disturbance in the wards. Mainly with the one called Alec. Well sir the problem is with the color of your eyes. They feel that you are of a different race and not truly a Gerial. They do not feel a loyalty to an outside race that has moved among the ranks to gain a title larger then their own.” Maternic said taking the glass offered to him. “And you? Where do you stand, Mat?” Ryvian asked as he downed the rest of the glass. “Sir, it is my honor to serve under the son of the great Destri. My father was on his ship when it went down, although me and my mother was living back at Mekings, he was stationed out there. I am with you all the way, but I believe that the others, all good soldiers, are being riled up by Alec and his treason.” Mat said placing the glass down on the desk. Ryvian nodded to himself as Lily opened up the door of the tent. He smiled at her and she walked to sit next to him. Mat stood up and nodded to Ryvian, “Well I’d best be getting back with the rest. I can’t keep my eye on them if I’m here all night bothering you.” He started to walk out when Ryvian stood, “Thank you for the information, it will come into use.” Mat nodded again and walked out.<br>
