<br>
Ryvian was on watch and wanted to get a good spot to watch over the camp. The Galton was currently up against the mountains that he had grown up in. He felt more then safe, and was not afraid of anything coming on the Gerial lands to attack a small Galton. As he spotted a good high place with plenty of the soft grass that grew in the coastal breeze he started his way up the slow easy climb. Just as he reached the top of the hill, Ryvian thought he saw move over the top and around the other side. Without thinking, instincts taking over, he pulled the sword of the griffon from his shoulder and raced after the shape that crested the hill. <br>
<br>
Rylena was just scampering over the hill when the glint of a sword caught her eye. Instantly she was terrified and wished that she had an Avi to protect her from this. Looking around finding that there was no place to run in the flats of the plains, Rylena flashed an image of that sword running her through. Almost in tears Rylena was shaking and the last idea of survival rose to her mind. She had to fight back in order to survive. She was a cleric not a ward or Avi; she was full of doubt. Doubt for everything but her need to do this to save herself. Finally with a tear falling from her small face she charged over the hill.<br>
<br>
Ryvian was ready for whatever it was that he heard coming over the hill. He was already in his stance and swinging when the red hair burst over the top of the hill. He saw in slow motion as Rylena came charging over the hill straight to his sword. He shouted as her beautiful eyes turned large with fright as she saw that it was Ryvian and that he had his sword drawn at her. Ryvian tried to pull back his sword but could not move it enough and Rylena fell right on the blade. Ryvian had already dropped the hilt and caught Rylena in the air, the whole thing had happened so fast that he hadn’t the time to think what he was doing. Rylena was wailing and Ryvian looked back to the camp to find that with the wind that the sound would not reach the camp. He yanked the cloak off his back as he tore it and set it beside Rylena, and started to look closely at the wound. He saw the blade in one side and out her small back. Swearing to himself Ryvian looked down at Rylena’s sweaty brow. “Sweetheart I need to get a closer look at this wound, I will try to do what I can for you.” Rylena tried to smile up at Ryvian. Nodding Ryvian started to cut away the materials of her shirt with his knife that he pulled form his belt. As he cut the rest of the blood soaked material away, Ryvian started to mop up the blood with the strips of his shirt. “It will be alright dear. Does it hurt here?” Ryvian asked as he pointed around the areas close to the wound. Rylena cried out and nodded. He started to point further away from the cut and his hopes sunk when it ended at her waist. “Dear I am going to take out the sword, it might hurt, but it needs to be done, I will do my best to stop the pain after I have done this, I will work as hard as I can.” Ryvian was sweating with the effort of not screaming and running back to camp to get Lily. Rylena’s back arched up as she screamed in pain while Ryvian pulled the blade out. Tears streaming down Rylena’s face, she looked up at Ryvian. His face and eyes with their panicked reassurance kept her from falling out of consciousness. <br>
<br>
The black night without the moon was still as Rylena’s panting breath became all that Ryvian could hear. He had watched her eyes closed more than the first half of the night ago. He held her head in his lap as he stroked her hair listening to her labored breathing. He had bandaged the wound up as much as he could, but knew that if he didn’t do something soon she would pass on. He also knew that if he went to find Lily he would come back to a corpse, and moving her might kill her as well. Ryvian cursed the stars as they looked down lazily at them from the heavens. He looked down at Rylena and remembered the night that he lost his sister. He let his tears fall to the ground as he cried. Then he looked again to the stars; he would not let her die. He had lost one sister, and now that he had finally found someone that could fill her place after all these years he was about to lose her as well. He shouted in his rage and looked back to the wound. He had covered Rylena with the remains of his shirt. He tore it away and pressed his hands on the wound right below right breast. He focused all his energy on the wound. He pulled from the souls that he had collected thus far. He pulled his strength that he saved and tapped even his connection to the moon. He shouted as the power came from above and surged through his back into his hands. Ryvian shouted as the light enveloped him. He wrapped his arms around the girl and felt her body start to squirm under his embrace. He let her go and held her out at arms length to get a better look at her. He pulled the bandages that wrapped her small form and found that the gash was just a small line of pink. He smiled as Rylena touched the place where the wound was and smiled up at Ryvian. “How?” <br>
