e hard to take in right now, but I need to tell you something; well I need to give you something.” Lily went to her bags and shuffled around in them for a moment grumbling. Ryvian watched in silence while she pulled a small parchment. “This is something that your father told me to hold for you until you either needed to see it because you had stumbled onto it yourself, or when I thought that you were ready to take this.” Lily handed him the note and went back to her seat. Ryvian unfolded it reading it to himself. When he had finished; he sat there in silence. Lily was looking at the light from the fire outside their tent when she heard Ryvian speak. “I had a brother. And you knew all the time what I was?” Ryvian looked up with his eyes dazed and frustrated. Lily nodded, “Yes Ryvian I even knew your brother before he left. He was just like you, acted just like you, and even looked like you. Ryvian I’m sorry I never told you, but there are some secrets that are not supposed to be told.” Ryvian watched her eyes as they changed again to a hazel and back to red. Almost as fast as she could blink Ryvian had his sword out and tipped right at her face. She stared at it off the tip of her nose as Ryvian’s face twisted in a growl. “You are not the girl I once knew! What kind of demon has taken that beautiful girl and given me this in return!” Ryvian snarled as his fist turned white at the hilt. Lily looked at the sword and back to Ryvian’s eyes. She nodded, “I am the same Ryvian, but you must ask yourself, do you remember me the way I am or the way you thought I was?” Ryvian grabbed the hilt with his other hand as he moved it back to swing. Lily felt tears fall from her chin as she looked at him. At the back of the arc Ryvian stopped, “Tell me the truth and not twisted words with cunning puzzles.” Lily nodded once more and started to take off the blouse that she was wearing. <br>
<br>
Ryvian watched with his face set and sword arm ready to take off what looked like Lily’s head clean off. He snarled as she started chanting in the Darkling tongue. He had studied it in his free time at school. He didn’t understand the words, but knew the language. She chanted and chanted and then was surrounded by a soft glow. He stepped back a step wondering if he was making a large mistake and if the yaltin had fogged his mind. He felt that if he were wrong then Lily would kill him with her power, which she was building. He moved back further when she started to growl with effort. Then with a flash of light he shielded his eyes from the sight. Looking back he didn’t see Lily as he had expected to, she stood with the same long red hair and the same face and body, but different eyes and now with the addition of the wings of a Darkling! She stood with her arms out in front of the white feathery wings. Ryvian almost couldn’t believe he was standing there; he had to fight the urge to slap himself to see if this was a dream. This made the fact that he was the third child of an Avi bloodline born with the power of cleric and Avi. Power that would eventually tear his mind apart, seem like nothing. He was shocked and horrified and yet thrilled all at the same time. He looked at Lily’s hazel eyes and the wings. He hadn’t realized that he was on his knees and had dropped his sword. “Ryvian, my father was a Darkling, I never knew that until my mother told me at her death. I have learned to hide it though, my mother had a way to hide it and was constantly drained by the power of keeping the disguise up and now that she had died I have to hold it myself. This is what I am, but I want you to know one thing, I have learned much about both my histories and learned that even though all the Darklings fell, they were not all evil. I was born of the last Skyfire male Magjic, their king, and was given the great responsibility to find the scythe of the Skyfire gods, forged by the Drul in the days of light, to take the seat of power and eliminate the bad from the good in the Darkling race to let our true name be known once again” Lily pulled a light purple dress from her bags and threw it over her shoulders as her wings shimmered and then disappeared behind the veil of magic once more. Ryvian was stunned and all her could do was stand, turn, and walk back to his seat to sit down to think about what he had just heard. This was indeed going to be a hard trip for them all.<br>
