 sigh he lifted the bag off the bed with the sword and flung it over his shoulder. “Shall we be going?” He asked while looking over the room once more. She nodded and started to open the door. Before she could get it open a hand pushed it back closed. Surprised she turned and found Wade gazing into her eyes. She felt a shudder go through her of excitement. Wade was standing so close the two were touching, “First tell Ryvian that I am going with you, but do not call me Wade, call me Dean the Quick. He will understand and it will make my life easier.” She nodded and he kissed her again, like the kiss last night it left her weak and dizzy. She felt his arms go around her middle and pull her closer; she wrapped her arms around him as well. Then Wade picked up the bag again and let her open the door. <br>
<br>
Ryvian was busy talking to Lily about the use of magic and how it was powered when Rylena pushed her way between them. “Ryvian, I need to talk to you.” She said grabbing his arm and pulling him away from Lily. Confused and almost angry Lily turned back to the Galton to talk to them about the formation for protection and that they must also keep the new cleric Rachel inside the circle as well as keep things from getting to her. She walked over to Talidon and started to talk to him as well about combat tactics. She was trying to let him know that he shouldn’t always follow in his teacher’s steps because Ryvian had a power that Talidon was not born with, something that a Warlord was given; she made that up of course, but was trying not to frighten the young Avi.<br>
<br>
“Ryvian, I needed to tell you something.” Ryvian turned back to the Galton as they impatiently waited on their horses. “Yes Rylena?”  Ryvian looked around and thought he saw someone wandering around the troop. He figured that it was just another Avi that was waiting at the Keep for his Galton to arrive. “I meet someone last night. He, well he is an Avi and one without a cleric.” Ryvian looked back to her with a grin on his face. “Ah! Well if our little girl hasn’t got charm.” He said grinning. Rylena blushed a little, “Well I wanted to know if he could come with us; Talidon got to bring his cleric. So I was just wondering, his name is Dean the Quick.” Instantly the grin from Ryvian’s face was gone. “What did you just say?” Rylena was shocked at his reaction. “Dean the Quick.” She repeated. Ryvian looked back to the Gerial walking around. His mind traveled back to the time of his childhood.<br>
<br>
“So this is the job of the crew. I have seven Avi and their Galtons on this ship. My boat is more of a transport than a fighter.” Destri said as he pointed to the large underbelly of the ship at the towline. “See, it goes far below the surface of the water so that it can carry more Gerials for transport to outposts like the one in the Darkling territory.” Ryvian looked at the giant boat and saw the many wards and deck hands running about like an anthill that had just been kicked. The Avi all started to come down off the boat to the dock and line up in front of Destri. “Well son these are the Avi that are going to the outpost Zefi. There’s Fredrick of the Surf, Dean the Quick, Robert of Mekings. All of these young lads will be heading to make sure that the Darklings never get past the might Gerials.” Ryvian was glad that his father had let him follow along with him to the docks to oversee the loading of the boat. “Dad, I need to get back to town!” he shouted as the sun caught his eye. He was supposed to be back in town so he could take Lily to the beach and show her how to fish with a lance at midday, but it was long past midday. “Going to see your lady friend right? Tell her since her mother is going to Mekings for the next few days she can stay at our house. I wouldn’t want her to slow down her mother’s important duty in the city now.” Ryvian nodded and ran off back towards town.<br>
<br>
Ryvian then remembered hearing how there was a rogue in the outpost that lead to the fall of Zefi from Mettrich. Looking back to Rylena he half smiled and walked off to meet with this Dean the Quick. “Sir, I’m Ryvian the Surefooted son of Destri the Warlord of Delnor that ferried you to Zefi all those years ago.” Ryvian watched intently on the face as it turned to face him. It was the face of a battle hardened Avi, holding the signs of experience and sporting two scars to prove it, one ran directly down his right eye, the other just above the brow. The Avi bowed and Ryvian took in the armor he wore. It was not the Avi armor, instead of the green metal; this Avi Dean wore leather that seemed to be thick enough to deflect a blade, but still light. The Gerial nodded with a slight bow. “I understand that you will be coming with us as Rylena’s Avi. Well if that is true, then I welcome you to our troop, but let me get one thing straight.” He said leaning in close, “That girl is in your protection, and if anything happens to her I will personally see you fall on my sword. Do we understand each other?” With a nod Dean grinned, “Just like your father, and your brother. I will keep my eyes open, but you be damn sure to keep yours open as well. After losing one cleric,” he said pointing to the scars on his face, “I will be more careful. I hear we’re going to Ibium. You watch that pretty young lass of yours. The humans are more than just devious, they are cunning and also they are gutless backstabbing son of whores the lot of em all. So you watch your back as well as those of your Galton and family.” Ryvian was shocked and stepped back. This Dean seemed like a worthy Avi to have ride with him, even if he was not very trustable. Ryvian left Rylena and Dean to themselves as they saddled up so he could go and mount his own horse. They had an objective to attend to.<br>
