iling Ryvian caught the eyes of Dean. His smile was gone. He remembered the face, the voice. There was something about the whole thing that made the hair on the back of his neck stand on end. Thinking he was just being overprotective; he pushed the thought of Dean from his mind. But the feeling of anxiety would not leave maybe it was something else. <br>
<br>
“General Sir! I have no idea where we are!” shouted a cleric to a commanding officer of the Ibium defense unit. They had been out in the wilderness for more than three weeks and had lost their way through all the forest. The cleric had found the small group moving quickly, after the destruction of the outpost Zefi. She felt alone in the fact that she was the only female in the unit and the only Gerial left from Ibium. “Sir! I repeat, I do not know where we are!” The General looked back with a small grin. The forest cleared up ahead and there seemed to be some huts. “We’ve made it! Now men grab her! She is finally yours to do with as you please!” Emily did not understand what was happening as the humans grabbed her ripping the dress from her body and hoisting her up on their shoulders. She screamed and kicked but the men were taller than the Gerials and had longer arms. They held her up higher so that she could not inflict maximum damage. They carried her to a tent where Darklings poured out. “NO! Traitors! I should have known better than to trust human scum!” the men dropped her and she fell face down in the dirt. Not shy about her nudeness she stood up to face the Darkling in front of her. “Die Bastard!” she spat as she raised her hands. The smirk on the Darkling’s face made her a bit unsure, but she continued on with her spell. The sky darkened and fire rose from her fingertips. The humans around took steps back and gazed with swords drawn at the sheen of sweat that had formed on her tan skin. The effort of the power was almost at the peak and the air felt thick and heavy. She screamed as the fire built into a smaller compact ball. Almost about to release it almost about to gain the full power, the Darkling laughed and spread his wings. Emily focused the power and was about to fling it at the Darkling that moved closer to her with every forced breath, when she fell like a wall she had been pushing on had just given way, right into the open arms of the Darkling. “Come my sweet. I shall show you the pleasure of my tent.” He said as tears ran down Emily’s face. He licked them off her cheeks and started to lift her up by the bas of her knees. He picked her up and seemingly in a trance Emily wrapped her legs around his waist as he moved back into the tent. Outside the air grew back to normal and the men started to set up tents among the Darklings.<br>
<br>
Inside the tent Emily felt completely exhausted, yet unable to sleep. She relaxed and let the hands touching her move her body in anyway that they wanted. Mala Havoc set her down on the bed and spread her legs wide. He grinned at the lightly tanned skin and the delicately pointed ears. He leaned down and kissed one. “Darling, you will soon feel the delight of a Darkling.” He whispered in her ear as he licked the inside. Emily shuddered and seemed to come back to herself slowly. She felt the hands moving over her breasts and tummy. She moaned and was drooling with her pleasure when pain tore through her body. She couldn’t breath and couldn’t scream out. After what seemed like an eternity of the searing pain air was allowed back into her lungs and she could only cry with the air she gulped. Her senses had come back to her and she felt a body next to her. Turning her head she saw the Darkling eyes closed with an arm over her. With a quick glance outside she realized she must have passed out and the time had gone from midday to midnight. Trying to move she felt the pain rip through her lower body and had to bite her tongue not to scream. She rolled out of the bed landing on a floor covered in furs and maps. She stifled her shouts and went about her work. The moon was out and radiating through the tent flap that was left open for air. She felt for her magic and slowly started to heal herself. After her work had come to a finish she looked around for her clothes. Finding nothing but an oversized coat she slipped into it and hurried out the tent and for the trees before anyone would know she had gone. Running into a human she gave a quick spin of her magic and collapsed the sentry disappearing into the darkness. She had to just make it to the wall and she would be fine, everything would be fine.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Crawling in the swampy moss and still water, Emily had long given up her cloak for the ability to blend into the surroundings better. It seemed every breath she took was stilled quickly as a group of Darklings would trudge past her. When she could see the sky she looked to the stars seeing the moon. Falling into a deep puddle of muck water she pulled herself up onto the shore. Gazing up at the sky and moon she wished of all the people in the world that her brother would come and save her. She knew that it was just childish feelings, she had seen him killed at the fort and knew he would not come back. Tears fell from her eyes as the memory of the Darklings dropping him onto the roof of the compound she was in resurfaced. She closed her eyes and tried to think of a time when they were little living in a small town. They were in the province of Delnor, and were very poor. Her father was a ship captain in the city and helped patrol the coasts. Back then she was too young to remember well the memory of her parents. They died in an accident fire that broke out to the north of their home moving with the wind engulfing their home. She was sinking in the mud as well as her horrible memories when the voice seemed to come from above like the voice of a god. “Lass! What in the name of Drelphia do ya think yer doin’!” a gruff voice asked. Snapping out of her thoughts she looked up to see that the wall she had been searching for was right behind her and covered in thick moss. She had thought there would be a plain that would lead to it, at least that is what she remembered, maybe she was further west than she thought. With a wave she remembered that the she had not had water or food for nearly four days. She tried to stand up but failed and instead blacked out on the ground.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The sunrays broke through the tent and Rylena woke up with a yawn. She felt like staying in bed and sleeping for another day. That night she had barely gotten any sleep and was tired from her activities. Wade on the other hand was up and ready to go. “Sweet pea, it is time to wake up; we have a full day ahead of us.” Wade smiled when she threw a pillow at him. Ryvian ducked his head in to get a face full of pillow. “Reminds me of a few days ago when I graduated and Lily and I spent our first night together.” Grinning Wade started out the door of the tent behind Ryvian. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Emily was sleeping fitfully when she woke, sitting up. “Sorry to disturb yer sleep lass, was just tendin to yer wounds.” The stranger said. Emily looked at her surroundings and found she was still without clothes. The Gerial like creature sat next to her on the bed with a bowl of water and a towel cleaning the cuts and scratches she had gotten from her crawl here. She also found herself clean from all mud and muck with her hair cleaned. Slightly smiling she remembered that she was naked and blushed. She noticed the creature that was tending to her had the same ears of a Gerial and the same build, but his hair was light pale like sand and his eyes were pale blue. This could not be a Gerial. Surprised and slightly embarrassed Emily just laid back and closed her eyes again, she could think of worse places, and even worse company. At least here this place was warm and the fellow had a kind smile and a gentle hand. Soon she felt his tending to her wounds stop and he started to massage her shoulders and arms. Feeling absolutely blissful she fell back to a sound sleep.<br>
