e at least a hundred people that resembled Gerials, moving out of the water. They were armed for battle and they were moving towards land. As he followed them he saw their destination, his camp. The Galton had already spotted them closing in and roused the camp. The camp was set up for attack; tents in a circle closely set together, fire in the middle and the wards tents outside the cleric and Avi tents. The wards were forming a semi circle around the tents first line swords second line spears and lances. Talidon was positioned in front of them standing beside Dean, with the clerics behind the wards next to the fire. Ryvian was in a full sprint charging towards the on coming battle. These people must have come out of the ocean he thought. He had remembered hearing about a race that had moved to the seas during the war of light. They were called the Teniols. Supposedly they were great fighters and could live under water. Ryvian was trying to remember their tactics and just as his memory kicked in he saw the second and third fork of the offense come out of the sand dunes behind him and further beyond the camp. Ryvian pulled his sword and readied himself for the battle. He would have to do this without Lily. <br>
<br>
With a shout the Teniols were on them. Lily had studied them at school and remembered their strategy, a forked attack, three prongs the first and largest then flanked by two smaller offenses. Terrified that they would be out numbered and surrounded, she started her summoning. The moon was waning this late in the year and power was fading, Lily hoped she had enough to force them to attack straight on. She felt pain in her right arm and remembered she had been looking for Ryvian; she was turning her thoughts on this when the power enveloped her forcing its way out. Shouting, Lily raised her hands to the sky and saw the ground to either side of the camp in a v give way and fall creating a large trench on either side. This would force the Teniols to attack straight on, maybe it would give them a chance. <br>
<br>
Ryvian shouted as another spear tore into his shoulder. Rolling on the ground to dodge any more spears, Ryvian felt his power fade, he hadn’t even started to fight yet. The main fork broke off and headed to the camp leaving about ten Teniol warriors to finish the job. Big mistake thought Ryvian as he drew his other sword. The Teniols pulled their long curved blades and started to advance. Ryvian felt a power grow inside him as he started in. Battle! The heat of the night and the attacks were fueling Ryvian to act. Swinging he blocked and started on his killing path, nothing would stop him, only blood would fill his need.<br>
<br>
Talidon screamed as a blade forced its way between his armor. He must fight to lead the Galton, Ryvian was gone and Dean had moved ahead of him. Fighting for air to fill his burning lungs Talidon focused on the power of the Avi, he handed over the reins to a Teniol he had killed and relaxed his mind to rest. Watching as if outside his body, Talidon fought and defended himself better than he could if he were controlling it. Almost giddy with the new insight Talidon began to shift through the mind of the other Teniols he had killed. Interesting, he thought as the history of the race unraveled before his eyes. <br>
<br>
Rylena tried to open the door to her power as Wade slumped in her arms. He had been moving in and out of the Galton’s ranks when a stray spear had caught him in the chest. Lily was standing next to him trying to coach Rylena through this ritual of her first healing with the Avi that she would spend the rest of her life with. She struggled to open the door and was growing frantic when Wade started to relax his grip on her hand. “No! Stay with me!” she cried as she slammed her mind against the closed door holding her magic. Screaming she tried again and again until she opened it slightly. The wave of power rushed out, but the door would not open the rest of the way, just a crack. She screamed as the power was tearing through her. Trying to focus it onto the wound her right hand lay over she gritted her teeth and slammed into and through the doorway. The power was blinding and overwhelming. She screamed in pain as the force rushed through her hands, fingertips and finally into the wound. <br>
<br>
Light burst from her hands and Lily smiled proudly as her student had bonded herself to this Avi. With tears of joy Rylena pulled Dean’s head next to hers and kissed him. “Don’t ever think of doing that again!” she cried. As soon as he nodded he lifted himself up and held the cleric close. Lily turned her attention to the battle, the wards were taking a beating and could only hold the shields up while the few that could rested only to throw themselves back into the fray. This was bad, Lily thought to herself. Where was Ryvian when she needed him?<br>
<br>
Staggering back into the camp Ryvian held his right shoulder as blood gushed out between his fingertips. He had done what he could do to fix it himself, but felt he only complicated the matter. He fell next to the fire and saw blood all over the wards lying next to him. “Sir, we can’t hold like this forever, these bastards are tearing us to pieces.” Shouted a ward that had a gash in his chest. They all wait for the clerics to get to them patiently holding on to what they had left. Ryvian looked up when a hand touched his shoulder and the pain numbed and left. Expecting Lily he looked up to find Rylena smiling down at him. He smiled back, but couldn’t hold it as the pain from the other gashes in his back flared. Rylena saw the blood from the shirt that he was wearing and shouted for Lily to hurry over. <br>
<br>
With a shock, Lily covered her mouth at the long gashes in the back of the Gerial she loved. “Ryvian! Don’t move I’ll fix it.” She cut the rest of the shirt away and placed her hands on the cuts. They quickly stopped bleeding and started to close. Lily pulled him around and hugged him. Ryvian mused with her hair as he started to stand. “Darling that was close, remind me never to leave you again.” He grinned as Lily smacked him on the shoulder, “I’ll never let you out of my sight again that’s for sure.” <br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Standing up, Ryvian saw the sun had already started to rise. Looking out over field of dead bodies of the Teniols, Ryvian felt a tinge of pity strike him. He started to look for the remains of the force, but they had already dissipated back to the sea. The Galton had not lost a single Gerial. Proudly Ryvian started his rounds among the wards telling them what a good job they had done and to sit by the fire to rest. Ryvian was just pulling on his armor next to the fire when he heard snarling and bitter curses coming from behind a tent. Curious he started to move to get a look at what the noise was about. Turning the corner of the tent he was shocked to find a Teniol girl tied to the post. She could not have been more than Rylena’s age. What could she have been doing out here, he thought. Looking at her clothes, she was dressed in armor and armed to the teeth by all the scabbards that lay empty at her thin waist. Searching the minds of those he had killed in the battle, Ryvian found one that recognized her. She was the little sister of one of the commanders, and the last living heir to the throne of the Teniol kingdom. Confused as to why they were out here, attack him, Ryvian searched deeper. Watching the events of the briefing Ryvian gasped and dropped the link to the commander’s mind. This had been a mistake! The entire operation had been a mistake, the Teniols were out on a training mission meant to be four leagues away from here, but carried by the current. They hadn’t even known they were in the wrong spot! Ryvian felt guilty and turned back to his tent. This had been a night of blood and death for no reason and he felt guilty for it all.<br>
