<br>
Tied down and blindfolded, Marian could do nothing but cry out and kick at air. She was the daughter of a King and this is how these people were treating her! She was outraged, but even more, confused. The patrol was supposed to be at a training mission last night, but instead they had stumbled across this little group of what seemed like Gerials on the beach. She thought they were Gerial because of their eye color, but they did not act like any of the Gerials she had ever met before. All the ambassadors she had talked with were kind and gentle people. These Gerials acted like the Karz barbaric and rude. The Gerial’s tent she was in had grabbed her out of her sleep in the middle of the night and dragged her into his tent. She kicked and screamed, but it didn’t seem to matter to him. She heard someone enter, not the one before. She had grown used to the breathing of the other one. She tried to keep the face of a warrior, like her brother had taught her. She bared her teeth and snapped at the intruder. Hearing him stop and stay still not moving for some time her thoughts began to wander. Her platoon had been formed to be the last prong and show their flanking ability. She had met a Gerial that her brother had nursed back to health that was with her. Marian wondered if she was still alive. Emily, that was her name, Emily. She was nice and perfectly enjoyable, unlike these monsters. Thinking she was probably dead the blindfold was pulled back from her eyes. She could see. She also felt the binds on her hands and ankles loosen and break. This was a stupid Gerial if any. After the way they treated her patrol, she was now being cut loose. <br>
<br>
Ryvian, knife still in hands, offered his hand to the Teniol. “What is your name?” he asked as she looked up at him. “If I tell you, it will be the last name you hear pig!” she spat at him. Stepping back some Ryvian turned back to Alec. “Then let’s have it, I hope it is worth my life.” Ryvian said sarcastically. “Marian.” She snarled at him. Leaping off the ground she smacked Ryvian in the side of the head with a rock that had been on the ground next to her. Growling with pain Ryvian stood back up and deflected the rock that was thrown at him with his arm. Blood ran down the side of his head. Running his hand through his hair he felt the blood, pulling his hand back he saw the wound was much worse than he had thought, blood covered his entire hand. Starting to feel dizzy, Ryvian felt the power start to fill his hands. This was a feeling he was growing more and more comfortable with. Returning his hands to his head he clinched his jaw shut and his eyes closed as his scalp started to mend itself. When he was done his eyes opened and he was mad. He looked back to Alec and then back to Marian. “Do you know who I am?” he said calmly giving the room a creepy air to it. “I am an Avi! I am Ryvian the Surefooted! Warlord of Delnor! I am the one that killed your brother! And if you kill me you kill him too! Well what is left of him.” He snarled. <br>
<br>
Marian cried out and sank to her knees. “So its true, you did kill him.” Sobbing she looked up to find Ryvian’s unforgiving eyes glaring back at her. “Did you kill Emily too?” She looked to the other Gerial; he must be a ward. He did not seem that bad compared to Ryvian. The Avi even healed himself, which was impossible! Looking back to Ryvian, Marian was surprised to find what looked like compassion in his strangely green eyes. I will let you live, if you promise to not hit me with a rock or anything from now on. Now just tell me what happened? That is all I wanted in the first place.” Looking back to the ward Marian was going to have to be cautious, this could be a trap. “He tried to rape me. He pulled me in here before you came, before I screamed and started to take off my armor. Then he, licked me.” She said disgusted and worried, would Ryvian side with his own ward and hurt her more, or would he turn a deaf ear to her screams, or maybe he would spare her anything else they could do to her and help her, although that seemed like a small chance. Her people feared the Avi; they were stealers of souls. He would most likely rape her himself and then leave her to the rest of his troops. Laying back Marian decided to take the pain and disgrace so that she could escape when the time came and come back to kill them all. If nothing happened, she might have to stay near to this Ryvian just to study his people, if he protected her then he would set a new standard for the Avi. <br>
<br>
