<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ryvian stood outside of Alec’s tent and heard the soft sobs. He had taken Alec and put him up in another tent. He decided to let her mourn her brother before he made his mind up about anything. He was staring out into the sea when a fleck of metal against the moon flashed in his eye. Thinking it must have been the armor of a corpse out on the beach. He would send a falcon to pass back and forth on the beach to wait for a search crew to tell them what happened so the Teniols did not declare war on anyone. His stare became more relaxed as the light played on the water was blurred. He caught the glimpse of the light again and decided to find out what it was. Pulling the griffon blade once more he scanned through the crystal that lay in the hilt. The vision flew towards the shiny thing. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The fatigue taking over her body, Emily fell to her knees and then fell on her back to face the sky. She pulled her short sword from her belt and stuck it in the sand next to her leaning towards the camp. When she woke she could follow the direction and get to the Galton. Tomorrow she would find the people that were in that camp and find if they were rogue or not. Tomorrow.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Surprised, Ryvian nudged the Gerial that lay sleeping in the sand. She moaned, but did not wake. Contemplating how she got out on the beach this far from home by herself, Ryvian lifted her into his arms and started to carry her back to the camp. He would get all this sorted out in the morning. This girl, and the young Teniol, all of it would be fixed tomorrow. <br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
The next morning the sun rose as it did every day, but this morning there was something strangely different. The birds and gulls that were heard every morning by the sea were nowhere in sight. Ryvian woke and expected to find Lily sleeping next to him; she was not. He sat up, rubbing the sleep from his eyes, Ryvian looked around the tent. He found her sitting next to the fire outside the tent. He walked up behind her and sat down beside her. Putting his arm over her shoulder, Ryvian turned Lily’s head to face him. She had tears in her eyes. “Darling, what is the matter?” Ryvian was shocked when she put her head on his shoulder and cried. Understanding that sometimes it is better to let the tears flow, he let her cry it out and held her. <br>
<br>
Emily was woken by the cries coming from next to her. Startled awake, she looked around. She was in a tent on a cot, not in the sand of the beach. Somewhat disoriented she lifted her head to see what the noise was. Surprised that she was looking at Marian sleeping next to her, Emily shook the Teniol awake. “Marian?”  Turning her head, Marian jumped out her bed with a shout. “You’re alive!” the two friends embraced each other. Marian explained their current situation and the two decided to wait it out and see how the dice rolled.<br>
<br>
The day had started and the Gerials were running about doing their duties and such things. Ryvian sat looking at his map following the path with his finger. He had the rest of the day to get to Lib and still be on schedule. Thinking about his current situation with the two newcomers. He was not sure if he could trust either of them. The two women looked like they were battle tested and the Teniol seemed to resent them, yet held a curious nature about her that confused the matter more. Having thought about the matter all night long, Ryvian had decided to let the two come with him to Lib where if they decided to continue with them then they would be allowed, but if they were determined to return home then he would let them leave at Lib. That way if the two were to leave they would still be in safe territory. <br>
